	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100106243771371><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100106243771371>RE: Most damaging class?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100106243771371#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=11387><span id= >Stuuk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 21st 4:53 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In order of damage over time:<br><br>Mage, Necro, Wizard - mana point per mana point a mage and his/her pet will out do everyone.<br><br>In order of fast damage and quick kill:<br><br>Wizard, Mage, Necro - You cannot beat the fast DDs that the Wizard can dish out.<br><br>In order of versatily:<br><br>Necro, Mage, Wizard - flexablity is the cornerstone of why Necros are considered - the class - for soloing.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having more options and strategies when fighting puts Necros ahead of their class.<br><br>Race depends on how you like to play but many consider gnomes the best sense they have the least problems getting into cities, personally I like regen of the iksar to help with health to mana spells, but having an extra pool of mana is nice for the erudites and flayed armor is not all that bad.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
