	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Alluring Sirens in the Ocean of Tears are probably the easiest experience in the game for your level.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's like the area was made just for you.  I spent last week alternating between the Sirens (for xp) and the Sisters of Erollisi (for cash), went from 11 to 16 and earned over 100pp in about twenty hours of playtime, and that was with the occasional trip to Freeport and Butcherblock to unload loot and small coins.<br><br>Even though you're only level 11, buy your level 12 spells (especially Bind Affinity, Convoke Shadow and Heat Blood) before making your way to OOT.  You'll save yourself a lot of time this way.  Make sure you have at least one or two full stacks of bone chips, too.<br><br>Taking the boat from Butcherblock Moutains, watch starboard (right hand side of the boat) right after you zone into OOT.  When you see the first rock, jump off and swim for it.  Once you hit level 12, you'll probably want to bind yourself on this rock, but for now just accept that you'll have a long CR if something goes wrong.  The truth is, you'll hit level 12 so quickly here, you'll be able to bind yourself before you know it.  That's why I suggest you buy your spells early.<br><br>Don't worry, there's no sharks around here.  You can safely swim all around these rocks.<br><br>From that first rock, turn right and swim over to the second rock.  Walk around to the far side and you'll see the third rock.  There are two Alluring Sirens and two Aqua Goblins.  If you see three sirens, or any Dragoons, you're looking at the wrong rock.  Keep walking around the rock you're on and you'll find it.<br><br>Don't even bother with the goblins.  They'll be green when you hit level 12, they will gang up on you, and the loot is not very good.  Summon your pet and tell him to "/pet guard here".  Walk down the slope until you can Poison Bolt one of the Alluring Sirens.   The sirens don't help each other, so only one will fly over to your rock.  Hide behind your pet and let him do the rest.  Watch his health carefully, as the level 8 pet can sometimes be killed by the sirens.  If he's taking too much damage, don't be afraid to run in and tank for him.  Once you have the level 12 pet, this will rarely be necessary.  <br><br>Once the first siren is dead, med up a little, rest your pet, and kill the second.  They spawn about 6 minutes after you kill them, so it's easy to kill both without much downtime.  Once you get to level 13 or 14, you can try to hit the sirens on the other rock, but these are a little different.  First, the two sirens high on the rock will help each other, so you'll need to time your pull while one of them is flying around.  The third, who is occasionally replaced by a dragoon, can be pulled solo.  Second, these three girls are invulnerable to non-magical attacks, so even if you need to tank for your pet you won't do any damage if you still have your rusty dagger.  <br><br>At levels 11 and 12, most of them will be yellow to you.  At this point, you'll probably be getting half a blue each.  Even at level 16, they were still worth just under a quarter of a blue to me.<br><br>If you get bored here, hop the boat or swim south to the island and sail to Freeport.  Sell your Mermaid Scales for about 5sp each.  If you don't have any backpacks, buy a few.  Then get back on the boat to Butcherblock.  Your first stop will be the Sisters of Erollisi island.  Run East along the shoreline until you see a tiny peninsula sticking out into the water.  Bind yourself here, then walk up the slope a bit.  Summon and station your pet here, then go looking for the non-named Sisters.  Hit them with a Darkness and Heat Blood then pull them back to your pet to finish them off.  Loot the belts, words, and blood, forget the halberds and meat.  <br><br>When you get bored here, or fill your backpacks with belts, get on the boat again and sell your loot in Butcherblock.  Then head back to the sirens and repeat. <br><br>I'm still working on the beyond 16 part, but the Warrens is fun so far  ;)<br><br>--Illyona<br>Gnomecromancer of Bristlebane<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
